// invalid for parser: MULTIPLE parse errors in one file, exercising the
// best-effort recovery (sync to next ';' / '}' after each error, keep going).
// The parser must report BOTH errors (not just the first) and still parse the
// good function in between. Each bad function has a distinct syntactic fault:
//   - bad1: a `let` with no name (just the keyword + ';')
//   - bad2: a `let` with no type and no initializer
// A regression where recovery stopped at the first error (single-error mode)
// would only report bad1; a regression where recovery ate the good function
// would drop it from the parse.
let;
fn good_between() -> i64 { return 1; }
fn bad2() -> i64 {
    let y;
    return 0;
}
fn good_after() -> i64 { return 2; }
